’Ù@0b6c887ddbd00249ed44485affa9fd5601e4238e78e0139e7d13ceb41b01c1d4Ú́Title: title: term query
Path: Examples
Content:
Get cursor position.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> term query (ansi cursor_position) --prefix (ansi csi) --terminator 'R'


```
Get terminal background color.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> term query $'(ansi osc)10;?(ansi st)' --prefix $'(ansi osc)10;' --terminator (ansi st)


```
Get terminal background color. (some terminals prefer 
``char bel``
 rather than 
``ansi st``
 as string terminator).
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> term query $'(ansi osc)10;?(char bel)' --prefix $'(ansi osc)10;' --terminator (char bel)


```
Read clipboard content on terminals supporting OSC-52.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> term query $'(ansi osc)52;c;?(ansi st)' --prefix $'(ansi osc)52;c;' --terminator (ansi st)


```
’Ù@c52d35af5bbe13a8d5fe75b2ad1685ad6bbd23bed4452ddbf737d66d16b15801ÚûTitle: title: term query
Path: Notes
Content:
Print the given query, and read the immediate result from stdin.
The standard input will be read right after 
``query``
 is printed, and consumed until the 
``terminator``

sequence is encountered. The 
``terminator``
 is not included in the output.
If 
``terminator``
 is not supplied, input will be read until Ctrl-C is pressed.
If 
``prefix``
 is supplied, input's initial bytes will be validated against it.

The 
``prefix``
 is not included in the output.
